[[File:VRChat Support.png|thumb|A loading screen showing VRRat with a link to a support page.]]
'''Loading Screens''' are a series of intermittent scenes that are shown when loading into the client or [[Special:MyLanguage/Worlds|worlds]]. It displays helpful banners about VRChat, as well as display a download progress bar.

== Overview ==
By default, the loading screen scene consists of a teal void with bubble-like particles floating around, but can be changed with Cosmetics.

In the center of the view point is a graphic showing various banners. Underneath, displays information about the world the user is travelling to. It includes the percentage of the world downloading progress, thumbnail and author. Below that, shows a "Return to Home" button to return to the user's [[Special:MyLanguage/Worlds#Home world|home world]]. If the user is loading their home world, and they click the "Go to default home" button, it will load into the [[Special:MyLanguage/VRChat Home|VRChat Home]] instead.

The download process is skipped if the world is in the content cache via preload or previously downloading the world. 

<gallery>
File:None.png|Entering VRChat Home with “Show Go Button On Load” disabled. No buttons displayed.
File:GO!.png|Entering any world with “Show Go Button On Load” enabled. “Go!”
File:Return to Home.png|Entering a non-VRChat Home that is not a custom Home. “Return to Home”
File:Go to default Home.png|Entering a non-VRChat Home that is a custom Home. “Go to default Home”
</gallery>

After downloading, the loading screen will display the thumbnail of the world with a load indicator below it. The load indicator states progress in this order: 

* "'''Initializing World...'''", "'''Connecting...'''", "'''Joining...'''", and "'''Almost Done!'''"<small>{verify}</small> if the loading takes too long.

While in VR, you are able to see a mirrored version of the loading screen by looking behind.

